Xi Jinping sends a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum - Xinhua News Agency
On December 11, President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum.
Xi Jinping pointed out that today the world is experiencing unprecedented changes in a century, global technological innovation is entering an intense period, and the new round of technological revolution and industrial transformation have had a profound impact on the global economic structure.
The Greater Bay Area of Guangdong, Hong Kong and Macau should strategically position itself around building an international center for scientific and technological innovation and strive to construct a highland for global scientific and technological innovation to facilitate the development of emerging industries.
China is willing to work with scientists from all over the world and international scientific and technological organizations to closely exchange and cooperate in science and technology, strengthen research on major scientific issues, promote the joint cracking of common scientific and technological issues, deepen collaborative efforts on key scientific projects, jointly promote the development of the world's scientific endeavors, and better benefit human kind.
The 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum opened on the same day in Guangzhou, Guangdong Province, with the theme of "Exploring the Future, Sharing Science", and hosted by the Guangdong Provincial People's Government.
